# Web-deploy

A tool to automatic deployment of web projects (e.g. django based)


## Usage

Test files in project

Content of "**fabfile.py**":

```python
   
    from fabric.api import env
    from web_deploy import *
    from web_deploy.python import *
    

    def foo(tag=None):
        env.host_string = 'prod.or.test.example.com'
        env.use_ssh_config = True
    
        project_name = 'my_project'
        project_root = '/home/user/projects'
        virtual_env_name = '.virtualenv'
    
        db_dump_dir = project_root + '/%s/dumps/' % project_name
        app_dir = project_root + '/%s/www' % project_name
        dj_project_dir = app_dir + '/data'
    
        project_tree = (
            project_root + '/%s/public_files/' % project_name,
            db_dump_dir,
            app_dir + '1/',
            app_dir + '1/data/',
            app_dir + '2/',
            app_dir + '2/data/',
        )
        log_files = (
            '/var/log/my_project/my_project.log',
            '/var/log/my_project/celery/out.log',
        )
    
        system = System(
            project_tree=project_tree,
            app_dir=app_dir,
            log_files=log_files,
            daemons=[
                Uwsgi(),
                Nginx(),
            ]
        )
    
        django_prj = DjangoProjectModule(
            git=Git(
                dj_project_dir,
                project_name,
                'git@github.com:s.ome-user/my_project.git'
            ),
            virtual_env=VirtualEnv(app_dir, virtual_env_name),
            system=system,
            db=Postgres(
                path=db_dump_dir,
                name='my_project_db',
                user='my_project_user',
                password='Gjy16|T7@xv/jz$)P&ta|EQ$Sz',
            ),
            py_rq=dj_project_dir + '/my_project/requirements.txt',
            apt_rq=dj_project_dir + '/my_project/apt-requirements.txt',
            manage_py=dj_project_dir + '/my_project/manage.py',
            collect_static=False
        )
    
        project = Project(
            system=system,
            modules=[
                django_prj,
            ]
        )
        project.update(tag)

```

Then you may just say in console something like ```fab foo:deployment``` 
and your prod/test server will be updated to the last version of **deployment** 
branch/tag. Or if you will say ```fab foo``` your server will be updated to the 
last revision of current branch. 

After fetching changes from git will be applied  all migration and restarted all 
specified daemons (*uwsgi* and *nginx* in example above).


## Installation notes
Important! Before install web-deploy package you should manually install fabric for python3.4

```
    pip install git+https://github.com/akaariai/fabric.git@py34
    pip install git+https://github.com/ygavenchuk/web-deploy.git
```
